:- encoding(utf8).
% Lore local da geracao 6
% Formato: pokemon_lore(ID, Texto).
:- multifile pokemon_lore/2.
pokemon_lore(650, 'The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.').
pokemon_lore(651, 'It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.').
pokemon_lore(652, 'Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.').
pokemon_lore(653, 'Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.').
pokemon_lore(654, 'It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.').
pokemon_lore(655, 'It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.').
pokemon_lore(656, 'It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.').
pokemon_lore(657, 'It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.').
pokemon_lore(658, 'It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.').
pokemon_lore(659, 'They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.').
pokemon_lore(660, 'With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.').
pokemon_lore(661, 'These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.').
pokemon_lore(662, 'From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.').
pokemon_lore(663, 'In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.').
pokemon_lore(664, 'When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.').
pokemon_lore(665, 'It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.').
pokemon_lore(666, 'Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.').
pokemon_lore(667, 'The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.').
pokemon_lore(668, 'The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.').
pokemon_lore(669, 'It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.').
pokemon_lore(670, 'It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.').
pokemon_lore(671, 'It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.').
pokemon_lore(672, 'Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.').
pokemon_lore(673, 'It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.').
pokemon_lore(674, 'It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.').
pokemon_lore(675, 'Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.').
pokemon_lore(676, 'Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.').
pokemon_lore(677, 'The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.').
pokemon_lore(678, 'When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.').
pokemon_lore(679, 'Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.').
pokemon_lore(680, 'When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.').
pokemon_lore(681, 'Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.').
pokemon_lore(682, 'It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.').
pokemon_lore(683, 'It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.').
pokemon_lore(684, 'To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.').
pokemon_lore(685, 'It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.').
pokemon_lore(686, 'Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.').
pokemon_lore(687, 'It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.').
pokemon_lore(688, 'Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.').
pokemon_lore(689, 'When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.').
pokemon_lore(690, 'Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.').
pokemon_lore(691, 'Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.').
pokemon_lore(692, 'They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.').
pokemon_lore(693, 'Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.').
pokemon_lore(694, 'They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.').
pokemon_lore(695, 'They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.').
pokemon_lore(696, 'This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.').
pokemon_lore(697, 'Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.').
pokemon_lore(698, 'This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.').
pokemon_lore(699, 'The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.').
pokemon_lore(700, 'It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.').
pokemon_lore(701, 'Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.').
pokemon_lore(702, 'Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.').
pokemon_lore(703, 'Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.').
pokemon_lore(704, 'The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.').
pokemon_lore(705, 'It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything.').
pokemon_lore(706, 'This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.').
pokemon_lore(707, 'These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.').
pokemon_lore(708, 'These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.').
pokemon_lore(709, 'It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.').
pokemon_lore(710, 'The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.').
pokemon_lore(711, 'Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.').
pokemon_lore(712, 'It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.').
pokemon_lore(713, 'Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.').
pokemon_lore(714, 'They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.').
pokemon_lore(715, 'They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.').
pokemon_lore(716, 'Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.').
pokemon_lore(717, 'When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.').
pokemon_lore(718, 'When the Kalos region’s ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.').
pokemon_lore(719, 'A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.').
pokemon_lore(720, 'This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.').
pokemon_lore(721, 'It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.').
